    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.17.1"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>    
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">UNITED STATES
                        <lb/>
                    DEPARTMENT OF THE INTERIOR
                        <lb/>
                    OFFICE OF INDIAN AFFAIRS
                        <lb/>
                    FIELD SERVICE</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Navajo Agency
                        Gallup, New Mexico
                        Jan. 10, 1936
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                    
                            <addrLine>Branson, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It has been my pleasure to read a number of your very excellent books on Indian life and I enjoy particularly reading and rereading "The Song of the Indian Wars".</p> 
                    
                <p>I write you, Sir, for a list of the books you have written on Indian life, with publishers, that I may purchase them for my library.</p>
                    
                <p>I have been in the Indian Service for some thirty years and you will know that I enjoy the literature that has to do with Indian life.</p>
                
                <p>It would be our pleasure to see you in the Navajo country at your convenience.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully,</salute>
                    <signed>C E Faris</signed>
                    <signed>C. E. Faris,
                    Superintendent.</signed>
                    
                    <note>CEF:CP</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
